olive oil
3 clove garlic
1 tin sweetcorn
20 g butter
1.25 cup water
1 packet jasmine rice
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet soy sauce mix
1 tsp rice wine vinegar
1 tsp sesame oil
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 bag parsley
1 bag Asian Stir-Fry Mix

• Finely chop garlic. Drain the sweetcorn. Heat a medium saucepan over high heat. Cook sweetcorn until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add the butter, a dash of olive oil and half the garlic, and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water and a generous pinch of salt to the pan and bring to the boil.
• Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low. Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender

and water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.
TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook Asian stir-fry mix and the remaining garlic until tender, 2-3 minutes.
Transfer to a bowl and cover to keep warm.

• When the rice has 10 minutes remaining, return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Stir-fry beef mince and sweet soy seasoning, breaking beef up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then return veggies to the pan, along with sweet chilli sauce, soy sauce mix and the rice wine vinegar. Toss to combine.

• Divide charred corn rice between bowls.
• Top with sweet soy beef and veggie stir-fry.
• Sprinkle with crushed peanuts and tear over parsley to garnish. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the garnish!